            <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                <h2 class="section-heading">About</h2>
                <h3 class="section-subheading text-muted">
                    For many teachers/professors, the struggle to get practical feedback on lectures, lesson plans,
                    and student comprehension relies on delayed tests and spotty individual feeback. However, the opportunity
                    to recieve real-time tracking of student understanding offers a revolution for proactive lecturers.
                    EvaluApp allows students to indicated understanding via individual app interfaces with real-time tracking
                    and questions displayed to the lecturer on a graphing interface.
                </h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-center">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-shopping-cart fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Assists Lecturers</h4>
                <p class="text-muted">
                All too often, teachers will stare at a sea of blank faces to wondering if the concepts 
                they are teaching are sinking in. Real-time tracking allows lecturers to maximize the amount 
                of time spent on introducing or reinforcing material and less wasted time covering concepts already understood. 
                EvaluApp provides a simple portal for organizing data on student comprehension of each individual lecture. 
                In the beginning of a class, the teacher will send out a unique link for the class. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-laptop fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Gives Students A Voice</h4>
                <p class="text-muted">                
                After entering their name (for tracking and attendance purposes), the student encounters a simple interface
                with prominent up/down buttons and an area to enter questions. As the lecture progresses, students will click
                either up or down to indicate their understanding of the lecture material. This feedback will then be returned
                to the professor in a simple graph that charts the collective level of understanding. Student questions are
                also transmitted to their display. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-lock fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Data Analysis</h4>
                <p class="text-muted">
                Particularly in large auditoriums or with shy students, educators will be able to easily understand what is 
                happening in their class as they progress through the curriculum.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

